The paper deals with the well-known clustering problem of $k$-means, which is a fundamental problem in both data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the uncapacitated facility location problem and $k$-median, which are optimization problems that fall under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). The use of local search algorithms is a common technique in theoretical computer science (cs.CC) for solving optimization problems. Finally, the paper deals with doubling metrics, which is a concept from geometry and topology that is often used in computer science (cs.IT).
